B21 - Design and implement a cybersecurity learning activity

Objective
The goal of this activity was to design and implement a simple cybersecurity learning activity to improve awareness of basic security concepts.

Method
I created a short quiz focused on key cybersecurity topics such as phishing, password security, and multi-factor authentication. The activity was designed to test basic knowledge and reinforce learning.

Implementation
A 5-question quiz was developed covereing common cybersecurity concepts. The questions were designed to be simple and relevant to everyday online usage.

Implementation
Strengths:
- easy to understand and accessible
- reinforces important cybersecurity concepts
- can be used as a quick learning tool
Limitations:
- limited depth due to short format
- doe snot fully assess advanced knowledge

Outcome
The activity showed how even simple learning tools can be effective in improving cybersecurity awareness. It also helped me understand how to design content that is clear and engaging.
